abstract: Ireland's largest political parties Fine Gael and Fianna Fail move past decades of acrimony to form Fine Gael-led minority government; agreement follows inconclusive February election in which Prime Min Enda Kenny of Fine Gael emerged without majority.
lead_paragraph: The agreement, which follows an inconclusive election and two months of political deadlock, is likely to result in the re-election of Enda Kenny as prime minister.

headline.main: Ending Impasse, Irish Leaders Agree on a Government
headline.print_headline: Ending Impasse, Irish Leaders Agree on a Government
